%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Interest%20rate%20cuts%20probably%20aren't%20here%20just%20yet%2C%20but%20they%20could%20finally%20reach%20Americans%20in%20under%202%20months%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jerome%20Powell%2C%20fed%20chair%20in%20front%20of%20federal%20reserve%20building%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a7bb20aab37011780b550a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20expected%20to%20hold%20interest%20rates%20steady%20in%20July%2C%20with%20cuts%20likely%20in%20September.%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20expected%20to%20hold%20interest%20rates%20steady%20in%20its%20July%20meeting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20it's%20looking%20more%20likely%20that%20rate%20cuts%20could%20come%20in%20September.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPowell%20said%20he%20wants%20to%20move%20cautiously%20to%20avoid%20cutting%20rates%20too%20early.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20safe%20to%20say%20that%20Americans%20can%20count%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-timeline-federal-reserve-inflation-powell-economists-forecast-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest%20rate%20cut%3C%2Fa%3E%20pretty%20soon%2C%20but%20probably%20not%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20will%20announce%20its%20next%20interest%20rate%20decision%2C%20and%20it's%20once%20again%20expected%20to%20hold%20rates%20steady.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECME%20FedWatch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20estimates%20probabilities%20of%20interest%20rate%20changes%20based%20on%20market%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eactivity%2C%20forecasts%20a%20roughly%2095%25%20chance%20the%20Fed%20will%20not%20change%20rates%20as%20of%20Monday%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20FOMC's%20September%20meeting%20could%20finally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseptember-fed-interest-rate-cuts-soft-landing-inflation-powell-su-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebring%20Americans%20the%20relief%3C%2Fa%3E%20they've%20been%20waiting%20for%20%E2%80%94%20CME%20FedWatch%20showed%20markets%20think%20it's%20all%20but%20certain%20the%20Fed%20will%20cut%20rates%20that%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECuts%20could%20be%20valuable%20for%20Americans%20struggling%20with%20high%20mortgage%20and%20credit%20card%20rates.%20Lower%20interest%20rates%20would%20make%20borrowing%20more%20affordable%20for%20consumers%20and%20businesses%20alike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed's%20high%20target%20interest%20rate%20%26quot%3Bis%20putting%20pressure%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20is%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20consumers%20to%20buy%2C%26quot%3B%20Claudia%20Sahm%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20investment%20management%20firm%20New%20Century%20Advisors%20and%20former%20Fed%20economist%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20to%20take%20out%20credit.%20It's%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20businesses%20to%20invest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20will%20likely%20have%20to%20wait%20a%20bit%20longer%20for%20those%20cuts%2C%20however.%20%26quot%3BA%20July%20Federal%20Reserve%20interest%20rate%20cut%20is%20unlikely%20but%20it%20will%20be%20debated%20and%20the%20decision%20second-guessed%20if%20we%20see%20weakening%20economic%20data%20over%20the%20next%20month%20or%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Greg%20McBride%2C%20Bankrate's%20chief%20financial%20analyst%2C%20said%20in%20written%20commentary.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fed%20will%20instead%20guide%20expectations%20toward%20a%20September%20rate%20move%2C%20pending%20continued%20improvement%20on%20the%20inflation%20front.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20released%20in%20July%20showed%20inflation%20continued%20to%20slow%20down.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-june-prices-food-energy-fed-interest-rate-cuts-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsumer%20price%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%20increased%203.0%25%20for%20the%2012%20months%20ending%20June%2C%20a%20cooler%20rate%20than%20the%203.3%25%20in%20May.%20The%20Personal%20Consumption%20Expenditures%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bea.gov%2Fdata%2Fpersonal-consumption-expenditures-price-index%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprice%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20showed%20how%20inflation%20is%20getting%20closer%20to%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target.%20The%20year-over-year%20increase%20for%20this%20inflation%20indicator%20was%202.5%25%2C%20just%20slightly%20cooler%20than%20the%202.6%25%20rise%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20been%20a%20rebalancing%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-rate-job-growth-june-economic-data-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Monthly%20job%20gains%20have%20been%20under%20300%2C000%20this%20year%2C%20except%20for%20the%20310%2C000%20in%20March.%20Plus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgdp-gross-domestic-product-second-quarter-2024-us-economy-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal%20GDP%20surged%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20an%20annualized%20rate%20of%202.8%25%20in%20the%20year's%20second%20quarter%2C%20far%20above%20the%201.4%25%20in%20the%20first%20quarter.%20Those%20numbers%20all%20point%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseptember-fed-interest-rate-cuts-soft-landing-inflation-powell-su-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20soft%20landing%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Fed%20is%20looking%20for%2C%20during%20which%20the%20central%20bank%20can%20fight%20inflation%20while%20avoiding%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20has%20shown%20the%20economy%20is%20moving%20in%20the%20right%20direction%2C%20inching%20toward%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20inflation%20target.%20Still%2C%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20has%20been%20clear%20that%20he%20does%20not%20want%20the%20central%20bank%20to%20move%20too%20quickly%20and%20cut%20rates%20too%20soon%2C%20running%20the%20risk%20of%20having%20to%20hike%20rates%20again%20at%20a%20later%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20loosen%20policy%20too%20late%20or%20too%20little%2C%20we%20could%20hurt%20economic%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said%20before%20the%20Senate%20Committee%20on%20Banking%2C%20Housing%2C%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%20on%20July%209.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20loosen%20policy%20too%20much%20or%20too%20soon%2C%20then%20we%20could%20undermine%20the%20progress%20on%20inflation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20economists%20and%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20have%20been%20urging%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20rates%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20given%20the%20economic%20progress%20the%20country%20has%20made.%20Sahm%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20seen%20the%20US%20economy%20has%20been%20getting%20back%20on%20track%2C%20normalizing%2C%20rebalancing%2C%20all%20of%20the%20Fed's%20catchwords%20for%20some%20time%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20strong%20recent%20numbers%2C%20some%20commentators%20noted%20that%20the%20economy%20could%20slow%20later%20this%20year%2C%20pushing%20the%20Fed%20to%20speed%20up%20its%20rate%20cuts.%20%26quot%3BThough%20second-quarter%20GDP%20surprised%20to%20the%20upside%2C%20it%20holds%20that%20a%20downturn%20in%20the%20labor%20market%20or%20considerable%20financial%20market%20stress%20is%20much%20easier%20to%20envision%2C%26quot%3B%20Matt%20Colyar%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Moody's%20Analytics%2C%20said%20in%20written%20commentary%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BFor%20that%20reason%2C%20the%20Fed%20should%20start%20moving.%20After%20September's%20cut%2C%20we%20expect%20another%20in%20December%20and%20then%20a%20roughly%20quarter-point%20per%20quarter%20pace%20thereafter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocratic%20Sens.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20Jacky%20Rosen%2C%20and%20John%20Hickenlooper%20also%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20Powell%20on%20June%2010%20urging%20him%20to%20cut%20rates%2C%20saying%20that%20keeping%20interest%20rates%20high%20is%20%26quot%3Bthreatening%20the%20health%20of%20the%20economy%20and%20risking%20a%20recession%20that%20could%20push%20thousands%20of%20American%20workers%20out%20of%20their%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20kept%20interest%20rates%20too%20high%20for%20too%20long%3A%20it%20is%20time%20to%20cut%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.warren.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F2024.06.10%2520Letter%2520to%2520Fed.%2520re%2520interest%2520rates.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-september-not-july-inflation-federal-reserve-powell-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722331802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a7bb22a0fc5856d5983d90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-september-not-july-inflation-federal-reserve-powell-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Federal%20Reserve%20isn't%20expected%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates%20in%20July%2C%20but%20relief%20could%20come%20in%20September%20as%20inflation%20continues%20to%20cool.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey%2CMadison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-september-not-july-inflation-federal-reserve-powell-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stop%20the%20crackdown%20on%20coffee-badging%20%E2%80%94%20here's%20the%20real%20problem%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221558%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22two%20men%20walking%20and%20talking%20at%20work%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a3ddaaaab37011780aed75%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221169%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoffee%20badging%20is%20performative%20compliance%20in%20response%20to%20a%20performative%20expectation%2C%20writes%20Bonnie%20Dilber.%3Cp%3EWestend61%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEmployees%20are%20'coffee%20badging'%20by%20briefly%20showing%20up%20at%20the%20office%20and%20then%20leaving.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETech%20recruiter%20Bonnie%20Dilber%20says%20companies%20shouldn't%20be%20surprised%20by%20it%20and%20should%20focus%20instead%20on%20results.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEmployers%20should%20make%20in-office%20work%20more%20beneficial%20or%20drop%20the%20requirement%20to%20be%20there.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can't%20go%20a%20day%20in%202024%20without%20hearing%20about%20another%20workplace%20trend.%20The%20latest%20one%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-enforces-new-office-hours-rule-targets-coffee-badging-compliance-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoffee%20badging%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoffee%20badging%20is%20what%20employees%20do%20when%20employers%20ask%20them%20to%20work%20from%20an%20office%2C%20even%20when%20their%20work%20can%20be%20done%20remotely.%20Employees%20briefly%20show%20up%20at%20the%20office%2C%20%26quot%3Bbadge%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-still-coffee-badging-office-returning-home-linkedin-poll-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrab%20a%20coffee%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20complete%20their%20work%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20are%20people%20doing%20this%3F%20Well%2C%20often%20because%20there's%20no%20great%20rationale%20for%20why%20they%20need%20to%20be%20in%20an%20office%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they're%20actually%20more%20productive%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20have%20asked%20employees%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floud-quitting-job-rto-policy-bad-company-culture-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn%20to%20offices%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20remote%20work%20spread%20across%20tech%20and%20corporate%20America%20(and%20the%20world)%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20for%20some%20workplaces%2C%20this%20makes%20sense.%20Being%20in%20the%20same%20place%20with%20fellow%20team%20members%20may%20lead%20to%20more%20collaboration%20and%20stronger%20relationships.%20Early%20career%20employees%20may%20benefit%20from%20being%20in%20person%20with%20more%20tenured%20colleagues%20and%20their%20managers%2C%20which%20provides%20more%20opportunities%20for%20mentoring%2C%20coaching%2C%20and%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20isn't%20the%20reality%20for%20many%20employees%20who%20find%20themselves%20%26quot%3Bcoffee%20badging.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20they%20may%20find%20themselves%20sitting%20in%20an%20office%20on%20Zoom%20calls%20that%20they%20could%20have%20taken%20from%20home%2C%20or%20distracted%20by%20the%20busyness%20of%20the%20office%20leaving%20them%20to%20catch%20up%20after%20work%20when%20they%20get%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20my%20take%3A%20Bring%20it%20on.%20If%20there's%20not%20a%20good%20reason%20for%20employees%20to%20be%20in%20an%20office%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20employers%20should%20be%20surprised%20when%20they%20opt%20to%20stay%20home.%20Better%20yet%2C%20take%20steps%20to%20make%20coffee%20badging%20unnecessary%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20workplace%20is%20constantly%20changing%20alongside%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20Fifty%20years%20ago%2C%20remote%20work%20didn't%20exist.%20Today%2C%20there%20are%20entire%20companies%20worth%20billions%20that%20are%20remote-first%20and%20have%20no%20offices%20(for%20example%2C%20the%20automation%20company%20where%20I%20work%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fzapier.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZapier%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20the%20event%20management%20platform%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhopin.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHopin%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Modern%20tools%20make%20it%20possible%20for%20people%20to%20collaborate%20and%20be%20even%20more%20productive%20without%20ever%20leaving%20their%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20employees%20found%20the%20office%20to%20be%20a%20place%20that%20enabled%20them%20to%20be%20more%20productive%20and%20do%20great%20work%2C%20they%20would%20likely%20go%20in.%20If%20there%20are%20purposeful%20reasons%20for%20an%20employee%20to%20be%20in%20an%20office%2C%20then%20employers%20should%20require%20them%20to%20be%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20it's%20simply%20a%20requirement%20without%20any%20real%20purpose%3F%20Well%2C%20if%20the%20expectation%20is%20performative%2C%20I%20see%20no%20issues%20with%20employees%20responding%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-workers-use-productivity-theater-performative-work-to-look-busy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformative%20compliance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20encouragement%20to%20any%20employer%20who%20notices%20coffee%20badging%20happening%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EExplore%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20expectation.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Do%20employees%20have%20a%20good%20reason%20to%20come%20to%20the%20office%20and%20stay%20there%3F%20Are%20they%20working%20on%20things%20that%20can%20be%20done%20better%20in%20person%3F%20Are%20they%20working%20side-by-side%20with%20managers%20or%20peers%20they%20can%20learn%20from%3F%20If%20not%2C%20then%20consider%20ways%20to%20make%20office%20time%20more%20purposeful%20to%20incentivize%20employees%20to%20not%20just%20show%20up%2C%20but%20stay.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFocus%2