regardless%20of%20their%20wealth%20or%20employment%20status%2C%20and%20with%20no%20restrictions%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-people-spend-universal-basic-income-ubi-food-housing-transportation-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehow%20they%20spend%20the%20money%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMatthew%20Johnson%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20public%20policy%20at%20Northumbria%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20there%20has%20always%20been%20a%20connection%20between%20tech%20and%20UBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20popular%20because%20they%20realize%20that%20the%20consequences%20of%20the%20technological%20developments%20that%20they%20pursue%20are%20that%20lots%20of%20people%20are%20going%20to%20be%20put%20out%20of%20stable%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20clearly%20a%20business%20incentive%20to%20remove%20those%20employees%20and%20replace%20them%20with%20technology%20that%20doesn't%20cost%20them%20salaries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220140c4cb-b841-4577-bf98-7352e5a5e83a%5C%22%3EMaking%20AI%20work%20for%20everyone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20people%20developing%20AI%20think%20a%20basic%20income%20system%20could%20help%20mitigate%20the%20tech's%20negative%20impact%20on%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFigures%20such%20as%20Musk%20have%20backed%20the%20concept%20since%20at%20least%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20at%20the%20VivaTech%20conference%20in%20Paris%20in%20May%2C%20he%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bbenign%20scenario%26quot%3B%20of%20AI%20development%20would%20leave%20everyone%20jobless%20%E2%80%94%20but%20with%20%26quot%3Buniversal%20high%20income.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20fears%20are%20echoed%20by%20some%20of%20the%20tech's%20earliest%20founders%2C%20who%20are%20sometimes%20called%20the%20%26quot%3BAI%20godfathers.%26quot%3B%20One%20figure%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-godfather-geoffrey-hinton-universal-basic-income-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGeoffrey%20Hinton%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recently%20told%20BBC%20Newsnight%20that%20governments%20will%20need%20to%20offer%20basic%20incomes%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%20on%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20runs%20one%20of%20the%20leading%20companies%20in%20the%20race%20toward%20AGI%2C%20has%20also%20long%20supported%20UBI.%20Recently%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20CEO%20also%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Buniversal%20basic%20compute.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman%20presenting%20on%20stage%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a256d95a8a7bf049196e7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222801%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman.%3Cp%3EJason%20Redmond%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20said%20tech%20leaders%20were%20essentially%20trying%20to%20fix%20the%20real-world%20consequences%20of%20technological%20development%20that%20they're%20invested%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20the%20UBI%20push%20is%20partly%20down%20to%20%26quot%3Bconcern%20about%20the%20wider%20social%20consequences%20of%20their%20activities%26quot%3B%20and%20fears%20that%20their%20companies%20won't%20survive%20if%20society%20faces%20widespread%20unemployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2203c804b5-c613-477c-a5e8-d49d1157ffc8%5C%22%3EAvoiding%20a%20dystopian%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Santens%2C%20a%20key%20advocate%20for%20universal%20basic%20income%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20first%20became%20interested%20in%20the%20concept%20through%20a%20tech%20angle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20studying%20the%20future%20of%20work%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20technology%20on%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20Santens%20became%20interested%20in%20finding%20a%20way%20to%20make%20technology%20benefit%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20question%20was%2C%20what%20is%20the%20realistic%20way%20of%20making%20technology%20work%20for%20all%20of%20us%2C%20instead%20of%20leading%20to%20this%20dystopian%20future%20where%20there's%20a%20small%20percentage%20of%20rich%20people%20and%20many%20poor%20people%3F%20That%20thought%20got%20me%20interested%20in%20basic%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20already%20been%20impacted%20by%20automation%2C%20at%20least%20since%20the%201970s%2C%26quot%3B%20Santens%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20computerization%20took%20off%2C%20wages%20did%20not%20increase%20in%20the%20same%20way%20productivity%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20prominent%20tech%20figures%2C%20there's%20also%20a%20PR%20dimension%20to%20supporting%20the%20basic%20income%20concept%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20outright%20lying%20to%20say%20tech%20won't%20impact%20employment%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Santens%20said%2C%20meaning%20leaders%20need%20to%20suggest%20solutions%20to%20balance%20potential%20diminishing%20demand%20for%20human%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20been%20pouring%20funds%20into%20basic%20income%20research.%20He%20raised%20%2460%20million%20for%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-basic-income-study-results-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elargest%20trials%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20systems%2C%20including%20%2414%20million%20of%20his%20own%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experiment%20gave%20low-income%20participants%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20three%20years%2C%20no%20strings%20attached.%20The%20research%20found%20that%20recipients%20put%20the%20bulk%20of%20their%20extra%20spending%20toward%20basic%20needs%20such%20as%20rent%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20food.%20They%20also%20worked%20less%20on%20average%20but%20remained%20engaged%20in%20the%20workforce%20and%20were%20more%20deliberate%20in%20their%20job%20searches%20compared%20with%20a%20control%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227fbe6c66-dd1d-40f1-bac6-e3b703f2ea30%5C%22%3EA%20slice%20of%20the%20pie%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20another%20argument%20for%20sharing%20the%20spoils%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20models%20are%20only%20as%20good%20as%20the%20data%20they're%20trained%20on%20%E2%80%94something%20that%20has%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20thorny%20issue%20for%20companies%20such%20as%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman's%20company%20and%20others%20are%20locked%20in%20a%20number%20of%20legal%20disputes%20over%20the%20right%20to%20use%20copyrighted%20content%20in%20training%20data%20for%20its%20large%20language%20models%20(LLMs)%20without%20payment.%20(OpenAI%20has%20a%20deal%20with%20Axel%20Springer%20that%20allows%20ChatGPT%20to%20summarize%20and%20answer%20user%20queries%20based%20on%20select%20content%20from%20BI%20and%20its%20other%20outlets%20including%20Politico.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20or%20not%2C%20most%20AI%20models%20are%20likely%20trained%20on%20content%20scraped%20from%20the%20internet%2C%20some%20of%20which%20belong%20to%20creators%20or%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20created%20the%20data%20for%20AI%2C%20so%20we%20all%20should%20benefit%20from%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Santens%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aaa818b7-3b82-417d-a6dd-d7502abd94bd%5C%22%3ESharing%20LLMs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20has%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20sharing%20the%20computing%20capacity%20of%20large%20language%20models%20as%20another%20form%20of%20basic%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20gets%20like%20a%20slice%20of%20GPT-7's%20compute%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20%26quot%3BAll-In%26quot%3B%20podcast%20in%20May.%20%26quot%3BThey%20can%20use%20it%2C%20they%20can%20resell%20it%2C%20they%20can%20donate%20it%20to%20somebody%20to%20use%20for%20cancer%20research.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20that%20as%20AI%20becomes%20more%20advanced%20and%20embedded%20into%20more%20facets%20of%20our%20lives%2C%20owning%20a%20unit%20of%20future%20large%20language%20models%20could%20be%20more%20valuable%20than%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnna%20Yelizarova%2C%20a%20project%20lead%20at%20the%20Future%20of%20Life%20Institute%2C%20said%20tech%20companies%20have%20discussed%20sharing%20access%20to%20the%20AI%20models%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20conversation%20has%20been%20more%20around%20access%20to%20compute%20or%20access%20to%20the%20models%20themselves%2C%20which%20is%20a%20great%20start%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20if%20we%20really%20do%20get%20AI%20technology%20that%20can%20replace%20intellectual%20human%20labor%20at%20scale%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20think%20of%20new%20approaches%20to%20ensure%20that%20economic%20gains%20are%20really%20evenly%20distributed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fubi-universal-basic-income-ai-risks-destroying-jobs-solutions-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722330002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66993d0d80d4d5da13d4fd4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fubi-universal-basic-income-ai-risks-destroying-jobs-solutions-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Figures%20including%20Sam%20Altman%20think%20a%20form%20of%20universal%20basic%20income%2C%20or%20UBI%2C%20could%20be%20a%20solution%20if%20artificial%20intelligence%20starts%20destroying%20jobs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bnolan%40insider.com%20(Beatrice%20Nolan)