ng%20the%20Koreans%2016-10%20in%20the%20bronze%20medal%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20Indian%20athlete%20to%20have%20won%20two%20medals%20in%20a%20single%20Olympics%20campaign%20is%20Norman%20Pritchard%20won%20two%20silver%20medals%20in%20athletics%20during%20the%201900%20Games%20when%20India%20was%20under%20British%20rule.%20After%20Pritchard%2C%20no%20Indian%20athlete%20has%20managed%20to%20win%20two%20medals%20in%20a%20single%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20couple%20of%20Indian%20athletes%20who%20have%20won%20two%20medals%20in%20the%20Olympic%20Games%20cumulatively%20in%20their%20career.%20They%20are%20Sushil%20Kumar%20(wrestling)%20and%20PV%20Sindhu%20(badminton).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESushil%20bagged%20a%20bronze%20medal%20at%20the%20Beijing%202008%20games%20before%20earning%20a%20silver%20medal%20at%20London%202012.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20he%20became%20the%20first-ever%20individual%20athlete%20from%20India%20to%20win%20multiple%20Olympic%20medals%20post-independence%2C%20over%20two%20different%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShuttler%20Sindhu%20won%20silver%20in%20the%20Rio%20Olympics%2C%20after%20being%20beaten%20by%20Spain's%20Carolina%20Marin%20in%20the%20final.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20time%20that%20India%20had%20won%20a%20silver%20medal%20in%20Olympic%20badminton.%20Sindh%20later%20won%20bronze%20at%20Tokyo%202020.%20Sindhu%20is%20the%20only%20woman%20athlete%20from%20India%20to%20win%20multiple%20medals%20at%20the%20Olympic%20Games%2C%20though%20over%20two%20different%20editions.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722327660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fsnm14s4_manu-bhaker-and-sarabjot-singh-afp_625x300_30_July_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Folympics-2024%2Fmanu-bhaker-bags-second-bronze-in-paris-olympics-earns-historic-first-for-independent-india-6221436%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Manu%20Bhaker%20and%20Sarabjot%20Singh%20earned%20a%20bronze%20medal%20in%20mixe