s%20Auckland%20house%2C%20where%20police%20discovered%20%26quot%3Ba%20number%20of%26quot%3B%20dogs%2C%20and%20given%20over%20to%20the%20SPCA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENuggi%20died%20of%20a%20liver%20haemorrhage%20even%20though%20it%20lost%208.8%20kilograms%20(19.6%20pounds)%20or%20around%2016.5%20per%20cent%20of%20his%20body%20weight%20in%20two%20months%20while%20in%20the%20care%20of%20the%20SPCA.%20The%20organisation%20claims%20that%20an%20autopsy%20disclosed%20additional%20health%20issues%2C%20including%20Cushing's%20illness%20and%20liver%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20statement%2C%20the%20owner%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20failing%20to%20provide%20for%20the%20dog's%20medical%2C%20behavioural%2C%20and%20physical%20needs.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20Manukau%20District%20Court%20in%20Auckland%20sentenced%20the%20owner%20to%20two%20months%20in%20jail%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20%241%2C222%20NZD%20(%24720).%20It%20is%20also%20said%20that%20she%20will%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20own%20dogs%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVeterinarians%20using%20a%20stethoscope%20were%20unable%20to%20detect%20Nuggi's%20heartbeat%20because%20of%20his%20extreme%20weight%2C%20according%20to%20the%20SPCA%20statement.%20The%20dog%20also%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20skin%20growths%2C%20especially%20on%20contact%20regions%20like%20his%20elbows%20and%20tummy%2C%20and%20his%20claws%20were%20enlarged.%20Further%2C%20Nuggi%20had%20conjunctivitis%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETodd%20Westwood%2C%20SPCA%20Chief%20said%20that%20the%20dog%20was%20%26quot%3Bdrastically%20overfed%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bclearly%26quot%3B%20did%20not%20have%20proper%20care.%20%26quot%3BNuggi%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20obese%20animals%20we've%20ever%20come%20across%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Westwood%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSadly%2C%20we%20see%20animals%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%20that%20are%20underweight%2C%20starved%20or%20malnourished%2C%20but%20it's%20equally%20heartbreaking%20to%20see%20a%20helpless%20animal%20that's%20been%20severely%20overfed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SPCA%20added%20that%20the%20pet%20dog%20was%20fed%20around%2010%20pieces%20of%20chicken%20every%20day%20along%20with%20dry%20food.%20Nuggi%20allegedly%20struggled%20to%20travel%20around%2010%20meters%20to%20the%20car%20when%20veterinarians%20took%20him%20away%20from%20his%20owner%2C%20pausing%20three%20times%20to%20gather%20breath.%20The%20SPCA%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BHis%20legs%20could%20not%20support%20his%20huge%20body.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20being%20a%20responsible%20dog%20owner%20is%20providing%20your%20pet%20with%20an%20appropriate%20diet%20and%20daily%20exercise%2C%20which%20was%20clearly%20not%20the%20case%20here.%20Nuggi%20was%20being%20drastically%20overfed%2C%20and%20instead%20of%20seeking%20help%20or%20amending%20the%20behaviour%2C%20his%20owner%20continued%20to%20overfeed%20him%20until%20he%20could%20barely%20walk.%20This%20is%20unacceptable%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Westwood%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722309720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2F4pt777mo_woman-sent-to-jail-for-overfeeding-53-kg-dog-to-death-in-new-zealand_625x300_30_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwoman-sent-to-jail-for-overfeeding-53-kg-dog-to-death-in-new-zealand-6219720%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Veterinarians%20using%20a%20stethoscope%20were%20unable%20to%20detect%20Nuggi's%20heartbeat%20because%20of%20his%20extreme%20weight%2C%20according%20to%20the%20SPCA%20statement.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwoman-sent-to-jail-for-overfeeding-53-kg-dog-to-death-in-new-zealand-6219720%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwoman-sent-to-jail-for-overfeeding-53-kg-dog-to-death-in-new-zealand-62